The paper discusses the design principles for improving the multi-core scalability of transactional database systems, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the limitations of current architectures and proposes a new system design, which involves advanced planning of transactions and separation of database component functionality, which falls under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC), operating systems (cs.OS), programming languages (cs.PL), and architecture (cs.AR).
